In [8]:

In [9]:

Noise_Vehicle=[]            
Posting_Advertisement=[]      
Traffic=[]                    
Vending=[]     
j=-1
for i in df_sub['Complaint Type']:
    j=j+1
    
    if i=='Animal Abuse':
        Animal_Abuse.append(df_sub.Request_Closing_Time.iloc[j])
    
    elif i=='Blocked Driveway':
        Blocked_Driveway.append(df_sub.Request_Closing_Time.iloc[j])
    
    elif i=='Derelict Vehicle':
        Derelict_Vehicle.append(df_sub.Request_Closing_Time.iloc[j])
    
    elif i=='Disorderly Youth':
        Disorderly_Youth.append(df_sub.Request_Closing_Time.iloc[j])
    
    elif i=='Drinking':
        Drinking.append(df_sub.Request_Closing_Time.iloc[j])
    
    elif i=='Graffiti':
        Graffiti.append(df_sub.Request_Closing_Time.iloc[j])
    
    elif i=='Illegal Parking':
        Illegal_Parking.append(df_sub.Request_Closing_Time.iloc[j])
        
    elif i=='Noise - Commercial':
        Noise_Commercial.append(df_sub.Request_Closing_Time.iloc[j])
    
    elif i=='Noise - House of Worship':
        Noise_House_of_Worship.append(df_sub.Request_Closing_Time.iloc[j])
    
    elif i=='Noise - Park':
        Noise_Park.append(df_sub.Request_Closing_Time.iloc[j])
    
    elif i=='Noise - Street/Sidewalk':
        Noise_Street_Sidewalk.append(df_sub.Request_Closing_Time.iloc[j])
    
    elif i=='Noise - Vehicle':
        Noise_Vehicle.append(df_sub.Request_Closing_Time.iloc[j])
   
    elif i=='Posting Advertisement':
        Posting_Advertisement.append(df_sub.Request_Closing_Time.iloc[j])
    
    elif i=='Traffic':
        Traffic.append(df_sub.Request_Closing_Time.iloc[j])
        
    else:
       
        Vending.append(df_sub.Request_Closing_Time.iloc[j])

The one-way ANOVA tests the null hypothesis that two or more groups have the same population mean. The test is applied to samples from two or more groups, possibly with differing sizes.

In [54]:
from scipy.stats import kruskal

The Kruskal-Wallis H-test tests the null hypothesis that the population median of all of the groups are equal. It is a non-parametric version of ANOVA. The test works on 2 or more independent samples, which may have different sizes. Note that rejecting the null hypothesis does not indicate which of the groups differs.
